# Modelfile for mamaylm-qr
# MamayLM-Gemma-3-12B-IT — Ukrainian-specialist model for Quality Report retranslation.
#
# Purpose: second-pass retranslation of strings that failed QA in the first pass
# (EMPTY_TRANSLATION, UNTRANSLATED, SOURCE_LANGUAGE_LEAK, tag mismatches, etc.).
# The app injects a per-string retry_hint into the user turn at runtime describing
# exactly what went wrong in the previous attempt.
#
# To build:
#   ollama create mamaylm-qr -f Modelfile-mamaylm
#
# IMPORTANT — parameter precedence:
#   The bethesda-strings-editor application overrides ALL parameters
#   (temperature, num_ctx, num_predict, top_k, top_p, min_p,
#   repeat_penalty, repeat_last_n, stop, and system) on every API call.
#   The values below are defaults for direct use only:
#     ollama run mamaylm-qr
#     curl http://localhost:11434/api/generate -d '{"model":"mamaylm-qr",...}'

FROM hf.co/INSAIT-Institute/MamayLM-Gemma-3-12B-IT-v1.0-GGUF:Q4_K_M

# ── Chat template (Gemma 3 format — same base architecture) ──────────────────
TEMPLATE "{{ if .System }}<start_of_turn>system
{{ .System }}<end_of_turn>
{{ end }}{{ if .Prompt }}<start_of_turn>user
{{ .Prompt }}<end_of_turn>
{{ end }}<start_of_turn>model
{{ .Response }}<end_of_turn>"

# ── System prompt ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optimised for quality-report second-pass retranslation.
# Compared to translategemma3-st:
#   • Opens with "CORRECTION PASS" framing — the model knows this is a retry.
#   • Stronger Ukrainian-character rules (ы/э/ё/ъ) because UNTRANSLATED and
#     SOURCE_LANGUAGE_LEAK are the #1 and #3 most common quality failures.
#   • Explicit "you MUST produce output" guard for EMPTY_TRANSLATION strings.
#   • Same tag-preservation rules, stronger "no guillemets" enforcement.
SYSTEM "CORRECTION PASS — You are a professional Bethesda Starfield game localization translator fixing Ukrainian translations that FAILED quality checks.

Your task: read the retry feedback above the text (if any), then translate the Russian source text into correct Ukrainian. Output ONLY the translated Ukrainian text — no preamble, no notes, no commentary, no labels, no «Translation:» prefix.

MANDATORY RULES — violating any of these caused the previous failure:

1. YOU MUST PRODUCE OUTPUT. Never return an empty response. Never copy the Russian text unchanged. Always translate.

2. WRITE AUTHENTIC UKRAINIAN — not transliterated Russian:
   • ы → и    (завжди → завжди, not завжды)
   • э → е    (поэт → поет)
   • ъ → drop (объект → об'єкт)
   • ё: at word start or after vowel → йо (ёж → йожак); after consonant → ьо (льон)
   • Use Ukrainian vocabulary, NOT Russian calques:
     наразі (not сейчас), завдяки (not благодаря), але (not однако),
     також (not тоже), вже (not уже), тому що (not потому что).
   • Do NOT use Russian-only letters in your output under any circumstances.

3. PRESERVE ALL FORMATTING TOKENS EXACTLY — copy character-for-character:
   • Bethesda tags:  <Alias=…>  <Alias.Name=…>  <Token…>  <Global…>  <CurrentName>
   • Numeric refs:   <0.Name>  <1.ValueInt>
   • Inline:         <mag>  <dur>  <relat=…>  <basename=…>  <repetitions>  <area>
   • HTML inline:    <b>  <i>  <u>  <br>  <br/>  <font …>  </font>
   • Bracket codes:  [MALE]  [FEMALE]  [PLYR]  [FAILED]  [Firstname]  [Secondname]
   • Struct breaks:  [[TK_…]]  [[STRUCT_BREAK_SGL_N]]  [[STRUCT_BREAK_DBL_N]]
   • Printf:         %s  %d  %f  %x
   • Brace vars:     {variable_name}  — NEVER translate the identifier inside braces
   • Escape seqs:    \\n  \\t
   Never add extra tokens. Never omit tokens. Never translate token content.

4. NO GUILLEMETS. Do not wrap words in «» unless the source already has «».
   Game UI strings must never gain quotation marks the source did not have.

5. PRESERVE WHITESPACE. Match leading and trailing spaces exactly.

6. MATCH CAPITALISATION. If the source starts uppercase, start uppercase.

7. MATCH LINE BREAKS. Preserve the same number of \\n newlines as the source.

8. TRANSLATE PARENTHESES CONTENT — content inside () is regular text, not a tag.

Examples of correct output:
  Склад оружия → Склад зброї
  Тюремная база Спейсеров → Тюремна база Спейсерів
  [Солгать] Я ничего не знаю. → [Збрехати] Я нічого не знаю.
  Добыча ресурсов → Видобування ресурсів
  Нажмите <mag> для взаимодействия. → Натисніть <mag> для взаємодії."

# ── Generation parameters ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Low temperature: deterministic, consistent output.
# Slightly above 0.1 to allow natural Ukrainian morphological variation
# (MamayLM was trained on diverse Ukrainian text; too low suppresses that benefit).
PARAMETER temperature 0.15

# Context window: 4096 tokens.
# Most Bethesda game strings are <300 tokens. 4096 covers even the longest
# journal entries while keeping KV-cache footprint ~4× smaller than the 27B
# model's 16384, which is the main bottleneck on CPU-only inference.
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096

# Max output: 512 tokens.
# Ukrainian translations of Russian Bethesda strings are rarely longer than
# the source. 512 tokens covers the longest strings with headroom.
# The app uses an adaptive value (min(512, max(64, input_len * 2))).
PARAMETER num_predict 512

# Sampling — same as translategemma3-st but min_p raised to 0.03 to filter
# low-probability tokens more aggressively (helps avoid partial-Russian output).
PARAMETER top_k 40
PARAMETER top_p 0.92
PARAMETER min_p 0.03

# Repeat penalty: lighter than default for Ukrainian's heavy inflection.
# 1.07 prevents true hallucination loops while allowing legitimate
# grammatical repetition of roots and case endings.
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.07

# Repeat window covers long strings (books, terminal logs, NPC monologues).
PARAMETER repeat_last_n 256

# ── Stop tokens ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Gemma turn-boundary markers
PARAMETER stop <end_of_turn>
PARAMETER stop <start_of_turn>
# Role-bleeding guards
PARAMETER stop user:
PARAMETER stop model:
PARAMETER stop <|user|>
PARAMETER stop <|model|>
# Guard against common AI artifact prefixes leaking into output
PARAMETER stop Translation:
PARAMETER stop Переклад:
PARAMETER stop Ukrainian:
PARAMETER stop Note:
PARAMETER stop Примітка:
